===subject:Reply to Edith
===from:Debbie Whiteman
===date:Fri Dec  6 13:44:56 2002
===message:Edith, I agree with most of what you are saying.  However, not all white people had a lot of money.  People without a lot of money still enjoyed a good family centered life.  It was a time of wholesomeness.  Movies and television were not even allowed to show married couples in the same bed.  The majority of families were two parent families. Parent's attitudes toward their children in school was certainly much different in the 50's.  Parents taught their children respect for teachers and other adults.  The parents supported the teachers; they didn't want to always blame the teacher or sue them.  Even though the fifties was a wonderful time for most children to grow up let's not forget that the minorites were still oppressed.
=========yorg=========
