===subject:Boom Time
===from:Eric Klausner
===date:Mon Dec  9  3:24:26 2002
===message:The video excludes minorities, but also gives the impression that all whites enjoyed the boom time.  In the 1950s there were white slums in the northeast cities.  The NYC melting pot was typically an overpopulated slum filled with whites, African-Americans, and Puerto Ricans sharing abject poverty.  Buildings were decades old with numerous families living in different apartments in which heat generated from radiators often failed to work.  Washing machines were in, but dryers were clotheslines hanging from windows in the tenement courtyard.  Air conditioning was a rooftop or a fire escape.  Transportation was feet, the bus or the train as few had cars.  Entertainment was stickball in the street.  Don't sound to booming to me.
=========yorg=========
