===message:I know it is a very sensitive issue when we talk about race in this country, and I also know that people forget so easily.  Those who felt they were left out on things would feel differently from those not affected.  It is a fact we also had other ethnic groups who were poor and did not enjoy the boom time, and to think that we have in this America to this day, places where some people are still using the “Traditional latrine system” instead of the water system, and they are supposedly living in a land of “plenty?”.  This is just a history class where the instructor asked us to narrate what was recorded, hence my mention of poor minorities and blacks; I hope it did not sound offensive to anyone. May I extend my regards to those of you who saw things as they were.  It’s been a fun class.  Hope we all make “A”s.
